President Obama issued a statement celebrating the canonization of Pope John XXIII and Pope John Paul II. He praised their work and influence, stating that Pope John XXIII revolutionized the Catholic Church's relationship with other faith communities through the Second Vatican Council, and Pope John Paul II played a significant role in ending communism in Eastern Europe and spoke out against apartheid in South Africa and genocide in Rwanda. President Obama also commended the leadership of Pope Francis and expressed his commitment to working with him and Catholics worldwide to promote peace and justice.